ndance based models were closest to the predicted specialization$\backslash$nfor GUA. The result of a similar pattern in predictability between sites$\backslash$nindicates that the influences of morphology and evolutionary and$\backslash$necological processes over the facilitation interactions are equivalent$\backslash$non a regional scale. Woody plant abundance was a key factor for the$\backslash$nfacilitation networks, driving forest expansion along the subtropical$\backslash$nforest-grassland ecotone.},
